<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-6078] Wrong memtable size estimation: liveRatio is not honored in edge cases</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-6078</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Memtable.getLiveSize does not honours liveRatio the correct way: &lt;br/&gt;
allocator.get**Size() return sizes allocated only by name and columns data (i.e. no liveRatio applied); but conditions, which cap estimated size, compare it with estimatedSize, already multiplied by liveRatio.&lt;br/&gt;
If liveRatio is big enough (i&apos;ve seen &amp;gt;11 on our dataset), this leads to huge estimation errors and even to OutOfMemory, because MeteredFlusher  underestimates memtables sizes.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12670024">CASSANDRA-6078</key>
